  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean a spray bottle before reusing it?",
  "response": "Cleaning a spray bottle before reusing it is important to ensure it\u2019s free of residue, bacteria, or contaminants. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to cleaning a spray bottle effectively:\n\n### What You\u2019ll Need:\n- Warm water\n- Dish soap or a mild detergent\n- White vinegar or rubbing alcohol (optional for disinfection)\n- A small brush or pipe cleaner (optional for scrubbing)\n\n### Steps:\n1. **Empty the Bottle**:\n   - Pour out any remaining liquid from the bottle.\n\n2. **Disassemble the Bottle**:\n   - Remove the spray nozzle, trigger, and any other detachable parts.\n\n3. **Rinse with Warm Water**:\n   - Rinse the bottle and all parts thoroughly with warm water to remove loose residue.\n\n4. **Clean with Soap**:\n   - Fill the bottle halfway with warm water and add a few drops of dish soap.\n   - Replace the nozzle and spray a few times to clean the internal tubing.\n   - Shake the bottle vigorously, then unscrew the nozzle and pour out the soapy water.\n\n5. **Scrub if Needed**:\n   - Use a small brush or pipe cleaner to scrub the inside of the bottle, the nozzle, and other parts if there\u2019s stubborn residue.\n\n6. **Disinfect (Optional)**:\n   - For thorough cleaning, use a solution of 1 part white vinegar or rubbing alcohol to 1 part water. Fill the bottle, spray through the nozzle, and let it sit for 10\u201315 minutes before rinsing.\n\n7. **Rinse Thoroughly**:\n   - Rinse the bottle and all parts with clean water to remove any soap or disinfectant residue.\n\n8. **Air Dry**:\n   - Let all parts air dry completely on a clean towel or drying rack before reassembling and refilling.\n\n### Tips:\n- Avoid using harsh chemicals or bleach unless absolutely necessary, as they can degrade plastic or leave harmful residues.\n- For bottles that previously held strong-smelling substances (e.g., essential oils or cleaning products), soaking parts in vinegar or rubbing alcohol can help neutralize odors.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure your spray bottle is clean and ready for reuse!",
